content.detailedDescription: Dennis thomas and i were flying a 185 wheel aircraft from crooked creek to aniakalaska.  enroute we flew over an object that appeared to resemble one of themilitary early warning site structures.  when we returned an hour or so later itwas gone.  i have personally flown the entire area on many occasions and thereis nothing, not even a beer can in the area.  i am now 56 as is dennis. i haveover 20,000 hours as a bush pilot in alaska.  i have seen more than most andthis has stayed with me.  i see dennis on occasion and we cant say much aboutthis. we are going to die with this knowledge and your site looks serious.Ps  im very inventive now.  see www.Greatlandlaser.Combest regardsjim omeara
content.summary: Flew over ufo on surfaceat 1000 ft

content.detailedDescription: thissighting, involved a corporate pilot based in iowa, who is also a certifiedflight instructor.  the sighting  occurred in september of 1984 at about 10:30p.M. (local time) in the skies over brazil about 90 nautical miles from rio dejaneiro, and lasted for some seven (7) minutes.  when this pilot witness (and his co-pilot) flying a c-p210 first saw somethingunusual, they were flying above the cloud cover at 13,000 feet altitude, lookingdown on a cloud cover at only 10,000 feet altitude.What they saw was a light illuminating the clouds below them, and - because thelight seemed to move in a somewhat see-saw motion from side to side - theyspeculated that it might be a searchlight.Suddenly the light/object came up through the cloud cover "very fast" and as itpassed by their aircraft and shot up into space they saw that it was atriangular shaped object (estimated to be about the size of a "truck," with redlights at each corner of the triangle, and a blue light in the center of theunderside of the object.It should be noted that this is not the only ufo sighting reported by thiscorporate pilot.  he indicates having sighted several formations of ufos - fromthe ground - while in europe.
content.locationName: Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro

We were driving home after dinner and we were in sight of our house. when werounded the corner there were many bright lights that all seemed to be a part ofsome craft. it looked exactly like an airplane with its lights on,without theairplane, but it just hovered therefor about a minute.We were all calm. thenjust as we turned at the intersection we had stopped at the object took off andit flew away in an upward curved direction with a heavy bank to it. when turnedon its side in its turn i saw the triangle shape. the flat bottom of thetriangle was the front and the point was the back. it dissapered quickly.

I was exiting the 5 freeway north at valencia blvd. in the city of valencia,california. i was viewing a construction site to the west of the intersection asit appeared to have something hanging high over it. the object was at a heightthat was far too high for a crane, but not high enough for an airliner. about1,500 feet altitude. the object was like a 727 airliner without wings or a tail.I watched it as i turned eastbound onto valencia and it remained stationary inthe air. i figured that the stationary illusion of the craft was a product ofreflection of the sunlight. however, it remained. i looked for a tail and wings,but it was apparent that there were none. i cannot guarantee that glare did notblock out these aspects. however, the odd thing was that the object remainedstationary.I am a practicing attorney who has absolutely no incentive to be labeled as someufo freak and an amateur astronomer. though i wear glasses, my corrcted eyesightis excellent.The morning gloom had burned off and the sky was hazy. in astronomy terms, theseeing was probably a 62b to 72b. there were no cloud formations in the sky.The object remained as such for approximately a minute and a half. after iturned, i still had a visual on it. i looked forward, then back and it was gone.It was no where in the sky.This observation should probably be used as corroboration of any other versusprima facie evidence of a sighting.

content.detailedDescription: I was contacted this morning by a person who wanted to file a report of asighting on 6303 at about 1035 pm just south the town of retrop, oklahoma 130miles west of oklahoma city 35.15n- 99.35w. the witness who is a radiologytechnician, was driving north on hwy. 6 and looked off to the west and saw 2objects hovering above a field. she states that the objects were between 30 and45 degrees above the horizon from her viewpoint. the witness stated she sloweddown and rolled her window down to see the objects clearer.Her description is that the objects were disk shaped, and had extremely brightwhite and red lights that flashed in sequence around the crafts. witness statesno stars or other aircraft were seen, this area is within the atc area for altusafb altus afb tower reported no air traffic in the area at that time. theobjects were seen for approximately 3 minutes before vanishing, as the witnesswatched. weather at the time of the sighting was reported to be good. no noiseassociated with the objects reportedwitness tried to find a farmhouse to stop at to try to get another person to seethese objects, however this was in a very desolate area and she was unable to doso. she did stop and contact 2 police officers in elk city when she arrived intown, she states she asked if anyone else had seen the objects, the officerslaughed at her, and then advised her to contact me. i have interviewed thewitness and she seems very credible.Jim hickmanmufon- research specialist for media operationsemail- jhickman1@prodigy.Net

It was july 1977 the time was close to midnight and i was returning home fromvisiting my sister who lived not more than 1.5 miles away.The skies were clear and stars very bright.  when i got within a 14 mile of ourhome i felt as if something was watching me to the extent that the hair stood upon the back of my neck.I then turned around slowly and noticed colorful lights in the nite sky forminga triangle.  since we lived close to fort drum new york, i thought it was amilitary aircraft.  however, it made no sound which made me suspicious.  i ranthe rest of the way home excited calling for my father who came with me outsideto view the thing from the blacktop of route 3.I needed some verification of what i was seeing.  his presence confirmed it.I have since been witness to events while serving in the us navy indian ocean,and a strange silvery orb the size of a basketball floating in the air thenjetting off into the direction of ft. drum.These events were years apart.  the military sighting during my time in the navywas photographed and documents  i suppose written  about the event.  there wasapproximately 30 wittnesses to that event alone.  aerial moves of wildproporsions.  no radar contacts, no sonar contacts... unbelievablehope this helps.

I was walking home from the train approx. 1 mile and i was looking towards thesouth east when i saw a silver disksaucer at about 10,000 feet with the leadingedge pointed slightly upwards and moving east.  i watched it for about 3-4seconds as it moved slowly and then there was a sort of blur and it disappeared. the saucerdisk seemed to be wobbling and it had what seemed to be notches thatwere evenly spaced around it middle rim or section as it wobbled and rotated.  ihad my camera with me but the sighting was so quick that it was gone before icould get my camera out.  it did not reappear.  i live in an area between theflight paths of laguardia and jfk airports.  i see regular jet traffic almosteveryday.  i actually live closer to jfk and so i see jets at lower altitudesgoing in for landing very clearly and also jets that are climbing to higheraltitudes after takeoff.  this object had no wings and i could tell it wascircular in shape because it rotated as it wobbled across the sky for that 3-4seconds.  the notches around the middle seemed to be small square or rectanglenotches evenly spaced around the object as it moved in its tilted up positiontowards the east.  thank you.

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i pulled into our home parking lot, apartments, and stopped toretrieve our mail. i just waited in the car, when i just happen to look up intothe night sky. i saw a larger object and several smaller objects following. igot out of the car and pointed them out to my husband. we were both stunned. anddid not think anything about it. just that is was very, very unusual. actuallydid give me chills. flashing lights came from all of the objects. the whole areaof the space they took up was hugelong. we had no idea what they were but put ifoff to possibily the military. we lived near stewart airport. we then got intoour car and drove up to our home.About half an hour later, i went to our back window, and just wanted to see ifthe objects were still there. and to my complete shock they were. they had movedsomewhat, but were very visible to our eyes. this gave me a chill and i couldnot sleep the rest of the night. this was not pilots as reported by stewartairport. these were not any airplanes that i have ever seen before. and whywould they still be in the sky after 40 plus minutes they were not triangledshaped as reported by the airport. and there had to be over 10-12 objects.To this day i am sorry that i did not report the incident. but....As you canwell imagine why.Thank you,sue  kevin lashombnew paltz, ny

My mother, great-aunt, brother,  i were returning to my great-aunts home innelson county,virginia during the time of the sighting. the year was either 1966or 1967,in the summer. we were visting relatives in the nearby town ofscottsville. it was still daylight, but in an instant it turned dark, as if godhad turned off a light switch. i looked out of the rear window of the car thought i saw lightning bugs fire flys. being a child i was surprised at thenumber of them. they first appeared in the trees  then in the field on bothsides of the road. i was so scared, i screamed  told my family about the lights.The odd thing is every time someone else in the car would look back, the lightswould be gone. it was as if they only wanted me to see them. i know this soundsodd, but its the way i felt  also the only explaination for the disappearingact. the orbs of lights moved onto the road behind us. they were hovering, everso closely to the road. the closer they got to us, the more fear i had. as soonas the lights first appeared my mother had difficulty getting the car to go anyfaster than 10 mph. everyone was frightened in the car, even though they didntsee the lights. i remember my great-aunt trying to turn her head around to look,but she seemed to move in slow motion  turned her head only slightly as if shewas being held back. i will never forget her face  how she screamed at my mom todrive faster. the lights made their way onto the back of the car. at this pointmy mom told me to lay down in the floor, so i wouldnt see them. after whatseemed like a few minutes, i calmed down some  sat back up. big mistake as i satup, i turned  looked out of my window. there right in my face was a light.
content.summary: 1966 or 1967 sighting of white orbs  missing time
